Deaf children in Arizona need your help! The Arizona legislature currently has two bills under review related to the future of the Arizona State Schools for the Deaf and Blind (ASDB). 

HB 2456 - re: the continuation of the school (Sunset bill). ASDB is set to terminate on July 1, 2023. Legislators will decide whether the school remains open for another 8 years. 

SB 1402 - re: the expansion of ASDB to become a school for ANY student with a disability. Legislators are recommending that ASDB no longer serve only students with sensory impairments. It would become a school for all children with disabilities: a) autism;
b) developmental delay;
c) emotional disability;
d) hearing impairment;
e) other health impairments;
f) specific learning disability;
g) mild, moderate or severe intellectual disability;
h) multiple disabilities;
i) multiple disabilities with severe sensory impairment;
j) orthopedic impairment;
k) preschool severe delay;
l) speech-language impairment;
m) traumatic brain injury; and
n) visual impairment.

Please share your thoughts in the comments, take action as outlined in the posts, and SHARE! Deaf children deserve better! 
