E.A.R. Day at A.T. Still University is a fun-filled time of education and recreation for deaf and hard of hearing children and their families. Hands-on activities led by audiology and speech-language pathology students provide a time and space for deaf kids to meet their fellow deaf peers and have FUN!

Deafinitely Communicating participated in this event for the first time as both a sponsor and exhibitor. We had a blast meeting families, networking with fellow exhibitors, sharing about our services, and spotlighting both Deaf-owned businesses and other families of DHH children through the resources shared on our table. 

